New World Resources, PKO Bank: Central European Equity Preview

-- B y   P a w e l   K o z l o w s k i   a n d   M a r t a   W a l d o c h
-- 
2011-08-23T22:01:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-23/new-world-resources-pko-bank-central-european-equity-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in central European
markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses after company names.
Share prices are from the last close.  Poland ’s WIG20 Index fell 0.2 percent, the Czech PX Index
declined 0.1 percent and  Hungary ’s BUX Index rose 0.2 percent.  New World Resources Plc (NWR CP): The largest Czech coking
coal producer will release second-quarter earnings. Profit
probably fell to 80.9 million euros ($117 million) from 129.6
million euros a year earlier, according to the median estimate
of 16 analysts surveyed by the company. Its shares fell 1.9
percent to 158 koruna.  PKO Bank Polski SA (PKO PW): Poland’s government suspended
a sale of shares in the country’s largest lender and will
reconsider the transaction at the end of October or in early
November, the Treasury Ministry said in a statement on its
website. PKO rose 0.9 percent to 36 zloty.  To contact the reporters on this story:
